Preheat the oven to 200C/180C Fan/Gas 6.Heat the oil in small frying pan over a medium heat. Add the onion and fry for 4–5 minutes, or until soft. Add the garlic, pepper and paprika and cook for 2 minutes.Stir in the tomatoes, tomato purée and salt and pepper, to taste. Cook over a medium heat for 10 minutes, or until the mixture begins to thicken.Transfer the sauce into an ovenproof dish, lay the fish on top of the sauce and bake for 10–15 minutes, or until the fish is cooked.Meanwhile, place the ‘courgetti’ in a microwave and cook on high for 2 minutes. Stand for 1 minute before serving with the fish.